  "prompt": "How do you remove your Gmail Profile picture?",
  "response": "To remove your Gmail profile picture, follow these steps:\n\n1. **Sign in to your Gmail Account**: Open your web browser and go to [Gmail](https://mail.google.com). Enter your credentials to sign in.\n\n2. **Access Google Account Settings**: Click on your profile picture or the circle with your initial in the top right corner. Then, click on \"Manage your Google Account.\"\n\n3. **Navigate to Personal Info**: In the Google Account settings, look for the \"Personal info\" tab on the left sidebar and click on it.\n\n4. **Change Profile Picture**: Under the \"Profile\" section, you'll see your current profile picture. Click on it.\n\n5. **Remove the Profile Picture**: If you want to remove your profile picture completely, look for an option that says \"Remove\" or a trash can icon. Click on it. You may be asked to confirm your decision.\n\n6. **Set a Default Avatar (Optional)**: After removal, Google may switch to a default avatar (an outline or colored circle with your initial). If you prefer, you can also choose to upload a different picture or simply leave it as the default.\n\n7. **Exit Settings**: Once done, you can exit the settings. Your changes will be saved automatically.\n\nRemember that it may take some time for the changes to reflect across all Google services.",
